title: 'It could've been a catastrophe': The Detroit Auto Show's move from January to June might have saved it from being a viral hub for coronavirus cases in the US
description: Bill Pugliano/Stringer/Getty Images Before being canceled outright over COVID-19, the 2020 Detroit Auto Show was permanently moved from January to June. The rescheduling most likely helped avoid what would have been a catastrophic outbreak of COVID-19, The De…
